{
  "stem": "20088.6",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I always feel a bit guilty about this, because I think if he would have known in the end after Heinz died, if he would have thought perhaps that my mother and perhaps I was still alive, he might have carried on.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He might just have survived.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because he died just two or three days before the liberation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But thinking that he would have been the only survivor, I think he just gave up.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I didn't know any better, and, you know, I just felt I had to tell him the truth, which I thought was the truth.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, of course, he-- I saw he was very upset, and he just said, well, try to be strong, and, you know, we'll come [? through ?] and we'll make a life again.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he knew that the invasion had been, and he knew the Russians [BACKROUND NOISE] were near.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was already towards the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We did know that it can't go on anymore for years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he tried to give me hope, and he said, in the kitchen, I've got a friend.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a very charming man, and he must have made friends with somebody in the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when you go there in the evening, she'll give you some extra food.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Which I did, and there was a-- was a Polish woman.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she said, your father is marvelous.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she always had some scraps of food for me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So, you know, it was really amazing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he-- he came another time, and that was really then-- twice he came, and that was the last day I've seen him.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I never asked him how he managed to find me or how he came there.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
